    h3.h3 Introducing the Chef Habitat Operator
    p.description
      | Kubernetes Operators are application-specific controllers that extend the Kubernetes API.&nbsp;
      | Use the Chef Habitat Operator to run and manage applications - built with Chef Habitat - on&nbsp;
      = link_to 'Kubernetes', 'https://kubernetes.io'
      | .
    div.row
      div.columns.small-12.large-6.np-left
        a.get-started--boxes--item.card.feature-card href="https://github.com/habitat-sh/habitat-operator"
          h4.h4 Learn about the Chef Habitat Operator for Kubernetes
          h6.h6 GITHUB
          p
            | The Chef Habitat Operator is a Kubernetes controller designed to solve running and auto-managing Chef Habitat Services on Kubernetes. It does this by making use of Custom Resource Definitions.&nbsp;
            | Explore the Chef Habitat Operator project on GitHub.
      div.columns.small-12.large-6.np-right
        a.get-started--boxes--item.card href="/docs/best-practices/kubernetes"
          h4.h4 Best Practices for Chef Habitat with Kubernetes
          h6.h6 DOCS
          p
            | Chef Habitat and Kubernetes are complementary: Kubernetes focuses on providing a platform for deployment, scaling, and operations of application containers across clusters of hosts,&nbsp;
            | while Chef Habitat manages the build pipeline and lifecycle of those application containers.

